es open for peer-review section <span aria-hidden="true" class="icon fas fa-chevron-down" data-v-10ba3bd0></span></a></div><div aria-label="Card containing the image, related theme, title, short preview, date posted, shareable links and altmetric score" class="card mb-80" data-v-10ba3bd0><div class="card-header" data-v-10ba3bd0><div class="card-img" data-v-10ba3bd0><div data-v-10f10a3e data-v-10ba3bd0><img data-srcset="https://asset.jmir.pub/assets/1b5f16692a76a3558aa69f32dc823818.png 480w,https://asset.jmir.pub/assets/1b5f16692a76a3558aa69f32dc823818.png 960w,https://asset.jmir.pub/assets/1b5f16692a76a3558aa69f32dc823818.png 1920w,https://asset.jmir.pub/assets/1b5f16692a76a3558aa69f32dc823818.png 2500w" alt="Article Thumbnail" title="Instagram Memes of Oral Nicotine Pouches: Content Analysis Study" aria-label="Article Thumbnail" src="https://asset.jmir.pub/placeholder.svg" data-v-10f10a3e></div> <div tabindex="0" role="button" aria-label="Open modal window to view the image" data-test="card-img-info" class="card-img-info" data-v-10ba3bd0><span aria-hidden="true" class="icon fas fa-search-plus" data-v-10ba3bd0></span></div></div></div> <div class="card-body mt-15" data-v-10ba3bd0><a href="/themes/1427" aria-label="Open theme with Infodemiology in Public Health Informatics" class="link card-theme" data-v-10ba3bd0>
                            Infodemiology in Public Health Informatics
                        </a> <div class="card-title" style="flex-grow: 1;" data-v-10ba3bd0><a href="/2026/1/e84025" data-test="card-title" aria-label="Instagram Memes of Oral Nicotine Pouches: Content Analysis Study" title="Instagram Memes of Oral Nicotine Pouches: Content Analysis Study" class="h5" data-v-10ba3bd0>
                                Instagram Memes of Oral Nicotine Pouches: Content Analysis Study
                            </a></div> <div class="card-info mt-20 mb-20" data-v-10ba3bd0><p class="card-info-text" data-v-10ba3bd0><span data-v-10ba3bd0>Oral nicotine pouches (ONPs), such as Zyn, have gained popularity among young people; however, their portrayal on social media remains under-studied. Instagram memes, a widely shared form of digital communication, may shape young people’s perceptions about ONPs and contribute to the widespread acceptance of ONP use.</span></p> <div class="read-more" data-v-10ba3bd0><a href="/2026/1/e84025" aria-label="Continue reading this article" class="continue-reading" data-v-10ba3bd0><span aria-hidden="true" class="icon fas fa-long-arrow-alt-right" data-v-10ba3bd0></span></a></div></div></div> <div class="card-date-social mt-6 pb-10" data-v-10ba3bd0><time datetime="2026-03-24" class="mb-0" style="margin-top: 2px;" data-v-10ba3bd0>2026-03-24
                        </time> <span class="mx-1" style="margin-top: 2px;" data-v-10ba3bd0>|</span> <span class="sm-icons" data-v-10ba3bd0><a title="share-on-Bluesky" href="https://bsky.app/intent/compose?text=Check%20out%20this%20fascinating%20article%20by%20%40jmirpub.bsky.social!%20https%3A%2F%2Fojphi.jmir.org%2F2026%2F1%2Fe84025" aria-label="Share this item on Bluesky" data-test="bluesky-button" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank" class="bluesky small"><span class="screen-readers-only">Share on Bluesky</span></a> <a title="share-on-Twitter" href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=Check%20out%20this%20fascinating%20article%20by%20%40jmirpub!%20https%3A%2F%2Fojphi.jmir.org%2F2026%2F1%2Fe84025" aria-label="Share this item on Twitter" data-test="twitter-button" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank" class="twitter small"><span class="screen-readers-only">Share on Twitter</span></a> <a title="share-on-Facebook" href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?s=100&amp;u=https://ojphi.jmir.org/2026/1/e84025&amp;quote=Check%20out%20this%20fascinating%20article%20by%20%40jmirpub!" aria-label="Share this item on Facebook" data-test="facebook-button" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank" class="facebook small"><span class="screen-readers-only">Share on Facebook</span></a> <a title="Linkedin" href="https://www.linkedin.com/feed?shareActive=true&amp;text=Check%20out%20this%20fascinating%20article%20by%20%40jmirpub!%20https%3A%2F%2Fojphi.jmir.org%2F2026%2F1%2Fe84025" aria-label="Share this item on Linkedin" data-test="linkedin-button" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank" class="linkedin small"><span class="screen-readers-only">Share on LinkedIn</span></a></span> <span class="card-altmetric" data-v-10ba3bd0><div data-doi="10.2196/84025" data-test="altmetric-link" data-badge-type="2" data-hide-no-mentions="true" data-badge-popover="bottom" class="altmetric-embed" data-v-10ba3bd0></div></span></div> <a href="#open-peer-review" class="skip-link" data-v-10ba3bd0>Skip recent articles and go to articles open for peer-review section <span aria-hidden="true" class="icon fas fa-chevron-down" data-v-10ba3bd0></span></a></div><div aria-label="Card containing the image, related theme, title, short preview, date posted, shareable links and altmetric score" class="card mb-80" data-v-10ba3bd0><div class="card-header" data-v-10ba3bd0><div class="card-img" data-v-10ba3bd0><div data-v-10f10a3e data-v-10ba3bd0><img data-srcset="https://asset.jmir.pub/assets/f531f808ba65f8e7fd78e3f3fb225316.png 480w,https://asset.jmir.pub/assets/f531f808ba65f8e7fd78e3f3fb225316.png 960w,https://asset.jmir.pub/assets/f531f808ba65f8e7fd78e3f3fb225316.png 1920w,https://asset.jmir.pub/assets/f531f808ba65f8e7fd78e3f3fb225316.png 2500w" alt="Article Thumbnail" title="Association Between Access to Health Information and Frailty in Older Japanese Adults: Web-Based Cross-Sectional Study" aria-label="Article Thumbnail" src="https://asset.jmir.pub/placeholder.svg" data-v-10f10a3e></div> <div tabindex="0" role="button" aria-label="Open modal window to view the image" data-test="card-img-info" class="card-img-info" data-v-10ba3bd0><span aria-hidden="true" class="icon fas fa-search-plus" data-v-10ba3bd0></span></div></div></div> <div class="card-body mt-15" data-v-10ba3bd0><a href="/themes/1417" aria-label="Open theme with Public Health Data Analytics" class="link card-theme" data-v-10ba3bd0>
                            Public Health Data Analytics
                        </a> <div class="card-title" style="flex-grow: 1;" data-v-10ba3bd0><a href="/2026/1/e83642" data-test="card-title" aria-label="Association Between Access to Health Information and Frailty in Older Japanese Adults: Web-Based Cross-Sectional Study" title="Association Between Access to Health Information and Frailty in Older Japanese Adults: Web-Based Cross-Sectional Study" class="h5" data-v-10ba3bd0>
                                Association Between Access to Health Information and Frailty in Older Japanese Adults: Web-Based Cross-Sectional Study
                            </a></div> <div class="card-info mt-20 mb-20" data-v-10ba3bd0><p class="card-info-text" data-v-10ba3bd0><span data-v-10ba3bd0>Older adults often access traditional media, such as newspapers, magazines, television, and radio, for health information. However, compared with older adults without frailty, older adults with frailty experience greater declines in physical functions and mental health (including depressive symptoms), as well as social functioning, due to reduced interaction with others, which limits their access to these sources of information.</span></p> <div class="read-more" data-v-10ba3bd0><a href="/2026/1/e83642" aria-label="Continue reading this article" class="continue-reading" data-v-10ba3bd0><span aria-hidden="true" class="icon fas fa-long-arrow-alt-right" data-v-10ba3bd0></span></a></div></div></div> <div class="card-date-social mt-6 pb-10" data-v-10ba3bd0><time datetime="2026-02-27" class="mb-0" style="margin-top: 2px;" data-v-10ba3bd0>2026-02-27
                        </time> <span class="mx-1" style="margin-top: 2px;" data-v-10ba3bd0>|</span> <span class="sm-icons" data-v-10ba3bd0><a title="share-on-Bluesky" href="https://bsky.app/intent/compose?text=Check%20out%20this%20fascinating%20article%20by%20%40jmirpub.bsky.social!%20https%3A%2F%2Fojphi.jmir.org%2F2026%2F1%2Fe83642" aria-label="Share this item on Bluesky" data-test="bluesky-button" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank" class="bluesky small"><span class="screen-readers-only">Share on Bluesky</span></a> <a title="share-on-Twitter" href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=Check%20out%20this%20fascinating%20article%20by%20%40jmirpub!%20https%3A%2F%2Fojphi.jmir.org%2F2026%2F1%2Fe83642" aria-label="Share this item on Twitter" data-test="twitter-button" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank" class="twitter small"><span class="screen-readers-only">Share on Twitter</span></a> <a title="share-on-Facebook" href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?s=100&amp;u=https://ojphi.jmir.org/2026/1/e83642&amp;quote=Check%20out%20this%20fascinating%20article%20by%20%40jmirpub!" aria-label="Share this item on Facebook" data-test="facebook-button" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank" class="facebook small"><span class="screen-readers-only">Share on Facebook</span></a> <a title="Linkedin" href="https://www.linkedin.com/feed?shareActive=true&amp;text=Check%20out%20this%20fascinating%20article%20by%20%40jmirpub!%20https%3A%2F%2Fojphi.jmir.org%2F2026%2F1%2Fe83642" aria-label="Share this item on Linkedin" data-test="linkedin-button" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank" class="linkedin small"><span class="screen-readers-only">Share on LinkedIn</span></a></span> <span class="card-altmetric" data-v-10ba3bd0><div data-doi="10.2196/83642" data-test="altmetric-link" data-badge-type="2" data-hide-no-mentions="true" data-badge-popover="bottom" class="altmetric-embed" data-v-10ba3bd0></div></span></div> <a href="#open-peer-review" class="skip-link" data-v-10ba3bd0>Skip recent articles and go to articles open for peer-review section <span aria-hidden="true" class="icon fas fa-chevron-down" data-v-10ba3bd0></span></a></div><div aria-label="Card containing the image, related theme, title, short preview, date posted, shareable links and altmetric score" class="card mb-80" data-v-10ba3bd0><div class="card-header" data-v-10ba3bd0><div class="card-img" data-v-10ba3bd0><div data-v-10f10a3e data-v-10ba3bd0><img data-srcset="https://asset.jmir.pub/assets/9ff8a5e291abed42f7a3d52c1c57a32d.png 480w,https://asset.jmir.pub/assets/9ff8a5e291abed42f7a3d52c1c57a32d.png 960w,https://asset.jmir.pub/assets/9ff8a5e291abed42f7a3d52c1c57a32d.png 1920w,https://asset.jmir.pub/assets/9ff8a5e291abed42f7a3d52c1c57a32d.png 2500w" alt="Article Thumbnail" title="Knowledge, Attitudes, and Perceptions Regarding Mini Implants Among Orthodontic Practitioners in the Kurdistan Region: Cross-Sectional Study" aria-label="Article Thumbnail" src="https://asset.jmir.pub/placeholder.svg" data-v-10f10a3e></div> <div tabindex="0" role="button" aria-label="Open modal window to view the image" data-test="card-img-info" class="card-img-info" data-v-10ba3bd0><span aria-hidden="true" class="icon fas fa-search-plus" data-v-10ba3bd0></span></div></div></div> <div class="card-body mt-15" data-v-10ba3bd0><a href="/themes/1417" aria-label="Open theme with Public Health Data Analytics" class="link card-theme" data-v-10ba3bd0>
                            Public Health Data Analytics
                        </a> <div class="card-title" style="flex-grow: 1;" data-v-10ba3bd0><a href="/2026/1/e86896" data-test="card-title" aria-label="Knowledge, Attitudes, and Perceptions Regarding Mini Implants Among Orthodontic Practitioners in the Kurdistan Region: Cross-Sectional Study" title="Knowledge, Attitudes, and Perceptions Regarding Mini Implants Among Orthodontic Practitioners in the Kurdistan Region: Cross-Sectional Study" class="h5" data-v-10ba3bd0>
                                Knowledge, Attitudes, and Perceptions Regarding Mini Implants Among Orthodontic Practitioners in the Kurdistan Region: Cross-Sectional Study
                            </a></div> <div class="card-info mt-20 mb-20" data-v-10ba3bd0><p class="card-info-text" data-v-10ba3bd0><span data-v-10ba3bd0>Mini implants, or temporary anchorage devices, have transformed modern orthodontic practice by offering stable, minimally invasive anchorage for complex tooth movements. Despite their proven effectiveness, their use varies widely across regions, often influenced by clinicians’ knowledge, confidence, and training.</span></p> <div class="read-more" data-v-10ba3bd0><a href="/2026/1/e86896" aria-label="Continue reading this article" class="continue-reading" data-v-10ba3bd0><span aria-hidden="true" class="icon fas fa-long-arrow-alt-right" data-v-10ba3bd0></span></a></div></div></div> <div class="card-date-social mt-6 pb-10" data-v-10ba3bd0><time datetime="2026-02-26" class="mb-0" style="margin-top: 2px;" data-v-10ba3bd0>2026-02-26
                        </time> <span class="mx-1" style="margin-top: 2px;" data-v-10ba3bd0>|</span> <span class="sm-icons" data-v-10ba3bd0><a title="share-on-Bluesky" href="https://bsky.app/intent/compose?text=Check%20out%20this%20fascinating%20article%20by%20%40jmirpub.bsky.social!%20https%3A%2F%2Fojphi.jmir.org%2F2026%2F1%2Fe86896" aria-label="Share this item on Bluesky" data-test="bluesky-button" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank" class="bluesky small"><span class="screen-readers-only">Share on Bluesky</span></a> <a title="share-on-Twitter" href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=Check%20out%20this%20fascinating%20article%20by%20%40jmirpub!%20https%3A%2F%2Fojphi.jmir.org%2F2026%2F1%2Fe86896" aria-label="Share this item on Twitter" data-test="twitter-button" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank" class="twitter small"><span class="screen-readers-only">Share on Twitter</span></a> <a title="share-on-Facebook" href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?s=100&amp;u=https://ojphi.jmir.org/2026/1/e86896&amp;quote=Check%20out%20this%20fascinating%20article%20by%20%40jmirpub!" aria-label="Share this item on Facebook" data-test="facebook-button" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank" class="facebook small"><span class="screen-readers-only">Share on Facebook</span></a> <a title="Linkedin" href="https://www.linkedin.com/feed?shareActive=true&amp;text=Check%20out%20this%20fascinating%20article%20by%20%40jmirpub!%20https%3A%2F%2Fojphi.jmir.org%2F2026%2F1%2Fe86896" aria-label="Share this item on Linkedin" data-test="linkedin-button" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank" class="linkedin small"><span class="screen-readers-only">Share on LinkedIn</span></a></span> <span class="card-altmetric" data-v-10ba3bd0><div data-doi="10.2196/86896" data-test="altmetric-link" data-badge-type="2" data-hide-no-mentions="true" data-badge-popover="bottom" class="altmetric-embed" data-v-10ba3bd0></div></span></div> <a href="#open-peer-review" class="skip-link" data-v-10ba3bd0>Skip recent articles and go to articles open for peer-review section <span aria-hidden="true" class="icon fas fa-chevron-down" data-v-10ba3bd0></span></a></div><div aria-label="Card containing the image, related theme, title, short preview, date posted, shareable links and altmetric score" class="card mb-80" data-v-10ba3bd0><div class="card-header" data-v-10ba3bd0><div class="card-img" data-v-10ba3bd0><div data-v-10f10a3e data-v-10ba3bd0><img data-srcset="https://asset.jmir.pub/assets/5fb3384834405f31eeb665e7cf39d267.png 480w,https://asset.jmir.pub/assets/5fb3384834405f31eeb665e7cf39d267.png 960w,https://asset.jmir.pub/assets/5fb3384834405f31eeb665e7cf39d267.png 1920w,https://asset.jmir.pub/assets/5fb3384834405f31eeb665e7cf39d267.png 2500w" alt="Article Thumbnail" title="Topic and Sentiment Trends in Semaglutide Discussions on X: Subpopulation-Based Longitudinal Analysis" aria-label="Article Thumbnail" src="https://asset.jmir.pub/placeholder.svg" data-v-10f10a3e></div> <div tabindex="0" role="button" aria-label="Open modal window to view the image" data-test="card-img-info" class="card-img-info" data-v-10ba3bd0><span aria-hidden="true" class="icon fas fa-search-plus" data-v-10ba3bd0></span></div></div></div> <div class="card-body mt-15" data-v-10ba3bd0><a href="/themes/1429" aria-label="Open theme with Social Media in Public Health informatics" class="link card-theme" data-v-10ba3bd0>
                            Social Media in Public Health informatics
                        </a> <div class="card-title" style="flex-grow: 1;" data-v-10ba3bd0><a href="/2026/1/e80660" data-test="card-title" aria-label="Topic and Sentiment Trends in Semaglutide Discussions on X: Subpopulation-Based Longitudinal Analysis" title="Topic and Sentiment Trends in Semaglutide Discussions on X: Subpopulation-Based Longitudinal Analysis" class="h5" data-v-10ba3bd0>
                                Topic and Sentiment Trends in Semaglutide Discussions on X: Subpopulation-Based Longitudinal Analysis
                            </a></div> <div class="card-info mt-20 mb-20" data-v-10ba3bd0><p class="card-info-text" data-v-10ba3bd0><span data-v-10ba3bd0>User experience has a significant impact on pharmaceutical drug effectiveness. Social media platforms like X (formerly Twitter) have become prominent spaces where individuals share their medication-related experiences, especially with widely marketed drugs such as semaglutide. Despite the large volume of conversation, a comprehensive understanding of how various user subpopulations engage with semaglutide-related discussions remains underdeveloped.</span></p> <div class="read-more" data-v-10ba3bd0><a href="/2026/1/e80660" aria-label="Continue reading this article" class="continue-reading" data-v-10ba3bd0><span aria-hidden="true" class="icon fas fa-long-arrow-alt-right" data-v-10ba3bd0></span></a></div></div></div> <div class="card-date-social mt-6 pb-10" data-v-10ba3bd0><time datetime="2026-02-24" class="mb-0" style="margin-top: 2px;" data-v-10ba3bd0>2026-02-24
                        </time> <span class="mx-1" style="margin-top: 2px;" data-v-10ba3bd0>|</span> <span class="sm-icons" data-v-10ba3bd0><a title="share-on-Bluesky" href="https://bsky.app/intent/compose?text=Check%20out%20this%20fascinating%20article%20by%20%40jmirpub.bsky.social!%20https%3A%2F%2Fojphi.jmir.org%2F2026%2F1%2Fe80660" aria-label="Share this item on Bluesky" data-test="bluesky-button" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank" class="bluesky small"><span class="screen-readers-only">Share on Bluesky</span></a> <a title="share-on-Twitter" href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=Check%20out%20this%20fascinating%20article%20by%20%40jmirpub!%20https%3A%2F%2Fojphi.jmir.org%2F2026%2F1%2Fe80660" aria-label="Share this item on Twitter" data-test="twitter-button" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank" class="twitter small"><span class="screen-readers-only">Share on Twitter</span></a> <a title="share-on-Facebook" href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?s=100&amp;u=https://ojphi.jmir.org/2026/1/e80660&amp;quote=Check%20out%20this%20fascinating%20article%20by%20%40jmirpub!" aria-label="Share this item on Facebook" data-test="facebook-button" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank" class="facebook small"><span class="screen-readers-only">Share on Facebook</span></a> <a title="Linkedin" href="https://www.linkedin.com/feed?shareActive=true&amp;text=Check%20out%20this%20fascinating%20article%20by%20%40jmirpub!%20https%3A%2F%2Fojphi.jmir.org%2F2026%2F1%2Fe80660" aria-label="Share this item on Linkedin" data-test="linkedin-button" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank" class="linkedin small"><span class="screen-readers-only">Share on LinkedIn</span></a></span> <span class="card-altmetric" data-v-10ba3bd0><div data-doi="10.2196/80660" data-test="altmetric-link" data-badge-type="2" data-hide-no-mentions="true" data-badge-popover="bottom" class="altmetric-embed" data-v-10ba3bd0></div></span></div> <a href="#open-peer-review" class="skip-link" data-v-10ba3bd0>Skip recent articles and go to articles open for peer-review section <span aria-hidden="true" class="icon fas fa-chevron-down" data-v-10ba3bd0></span></a></div><div aria-label="Card containing the image, related theme, title, short preview, date posted, shareable links and altmetric score" class="card mb-80" data-v-10ba3bd0><div class="card-header" data-v-10ba3bd0><div class="card-img" data-v-10ba3bd0><div data-v-10f10a3e data-v-10ba3bd0><img data-srcset="https://asset.jmir.pub/assets/0c472bcffd6d04fd1a2d6e8cb5e980a8.png 480w,https://asset.jmir.pub/assets/0c472bcffd6d04fd1a2d6e8cb5e980a8.png 960w,https://asset.jmir.pub/assets/0c472bcffd6d04fd1a2d6e8cb5e980a8.png 1920w,https://asset.jmir.pub/assets/0c472bcffd6d04fd1a2d6e8cb5e980a8.png 2500w" alt="Article Thumbnail" title="A Comprehensive Approach to Days’ Supply Estimation in a Real-World Prescription Database: Algorithm Development and Validation Study" aria-label="Article Thumbnail" src="https://asset.jmir.pub/placeholder.svg" data-v-10f10a3e></div> <div tabindex="0" role="button" aria-label="Open modal window to view the image" data-test="card-img-info" class="card-img-info" data-v-10ba3bd0><span aria-hidden="true" class="icon fas fa-search-plus" data-v-10ba3bd0></span></div></div></div> <div class="card-body mt-15" data-v-10ba3bd0><a href="/themes/1417" aria-label="Open theme with Public Health Data Analytics" class="link card-theme" data-v-10ba3bd0>
                            Public Health Data Analytics
                        </a> <div class="card-title" style="flex-grow: 1;" data-v-10ba3bd0><a href="/2026/1/e83465" data-test="card-title" aria-label="A Comprehensive Approach to Days’ Supply Estimation in a Real-World Prescription Database: Algorithm Development and Validation Study" title="A Comprehensive Approach to Days’ Supply Estimation in a Real-World Prescription Database: Algorithm Development and Validation Study" class="h5" data-v-10ba3bd0>
                                A Comprehensive Approach to Days’ Supply Estimation in a Real-World Prescription Database: Algorithm Development and Validation Study
                            </a></div> <div class="card-info mt-20 mb-20" data-v-10ba3bd0><p class="card-info-text" data-v-10ba3bd0><span data-v-10ba3bd0>For accurate medication usage statistics and medication adherence calculations, we need to have an accurate days’ supply (DS) for each prescription. Unfortunately, often the DS or the information needed for calculating the DS is not provided. Therefore, other methods need to be applied to acquire missing values or substitute incorrect values.</span></p> <div class="read-more" data-v-10ba3bd0><a href="/2026/1/e83465" aria-label="Continue reading this article" class="continue-reading" data-v-10ba3bd0><span aria-hidden="true" class="icon fas fa-long-arrow-alt-right" data-v-10ba3bd0></span></a></div></div></div> <div class="card-date-social mt-6 pb-10" data-v-10ba3bd0><time datetime="2026-02-11" class="mb-0" style="margin-top: 2px;" data-v-10ba3bd0>2026-02-11
                        </time> <span class="mx-1" style="margin-top: 2px;" data-v-10ba3bd0>|</span> <span class="sm-icons" data-v-10ba3bd0><a title="share-on-Bluesky" href="https://bsky.app/intent/compose?text=Check%20out%20this%20fascinating%20article%20by%20%40jmirpub.bsky.social!%20https%3A%2F%2Fojphi.jmir.org%2F2026%2F1%2Fe83465" aria-label="Share this item on Bluesky" data-test="bluesky-button" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank" class="bluesky small"><span class="screen-readers-only">Share on Bluesky</span></a> <a title="share-on-Twitter" href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=Check%20out%20this%20fascinating%20article%20by%20%40jmirpub!%20https%3A%2F%2Fojphi.jmir.org%2F2026%2F1%2Fe83465" aria-label="Share this item on Twitter" data-test="twitter-button" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank" class="twitter small"><span class="screen-readers-only">Share on Twitter</span></a> <a title="share-on-Facebook" href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?s=100&amp;u=https://ojphi.jmir.org/2026/1/e83465&amp;quote=Check%20out%20this%20fascinating%20article%20by%20%40jmirpub!" aria-label="Share this item on Facebook" data-test="facebook-button" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank" class="facebook small"><span class="screen-readers-only">Share on Facebook</span></a> <a title="Linkedin" href="https://www.linkedin.com/feed?shareActive=true&amp;text=Check%20out%20this%20fascinating%20article%20by%20%40jmirpub!%20https%3A%2F%2Fojphi.jmir.org%2F2026%2F1%2Fe83465" aria-label="Share this item on Linkedin" data-test="linkedin-button" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank" class="linkedin small"><span class="screen-readers-only">Share on LinkedIn</span></a></span> <span class="card-altmetric" data-v-10ba3bd0><div data-doi="10.2196/83465" data-test="altmetric-link" data-badge-type="2" data-hide-no-mentions="true" data-badge-popover="bottom" class="altmetric-embed" data-v-10ba3bd0></div></span></div> <a href="#open-peer-review" class="skip-link" data-v-10ba3bd0>Skip recent articles and go to articles open for peer-review section <span aria-hidden="true" class="icon fas fa-chevron-down" data-v-10ba3bd0></span></a></div><div aria-label="Card containing the image, related theme, title, short preview, date posted, shareable links and altmetric score" class="card mb-80" data-v-10ba3bd0><div class="card-header" data-v-10ba3bd0><div class="card-img" data-v-10ba3bd0><div data-v-10f10a3e data-v-10ba3bd0><img data-srcset="https://asset.jmir.pub/assets/665a654f27fa041b16888604667485bb.png 480w,https://asset.jmir.pub/assets/665a654f27fa041b16888604667485bb.png 960w,https://asset.jmir.pub/assets/665a654f27fa041b16888604667485bb.png 1920w,https://asset.jmir.pub/assets/665a654f27fa041b16888604667485bb.png 2500w" alt="Article Thumbnail" title="Associations Between Hospital Structural Characteristics and Adoption of Public Health Data Integration and Automation: National Cross-Sectional proofsStudy" aria-label="Article Thumbnail" src="https://asset.jmir.pub/placeholder.svg" data-v-10f10a3e></div> <div tabindex="0" role="button" aria-label="Open modal window to view the image" data-test="card-img-info" class="card-img-info" data-v-10ba3bd0><span aria-hidden="true" class="icon fas fa-search-plus" data-v-10ba3bd0></span></div></div></div> <div class="card-body mt-15" data-v-10ba3bd0><a href="/themes/1422" aria-label="Open theme with Public Health Information Exchange Technologies" class="link card-theme" data-v-10ba3bd0>
                            Public Health Information Exchange Technologies
                        </a> <div class="card-title" style="flex-grow: 1;" data-v-10ba3bd0><a href="/2026/1/e86263" data-test="card-title" aria-label="Associations Between Hospital Structural Characteristics and Adoption of Public Health Data Integration and Automation: National Cross-Sectional proofsStudy" title="Associations Between Hospital Structural Characteristics and Adoption of Public Health Data Integration and Automation: National Cross-Sectional proofsStudy" class="h5" data-v-10ba3bd0>
                                Associations Between Hospital Structural Characteristics and Adoption of Public Health Data Integration and Automation: National Cross-Sectional proofsStudy
                            </a></div> <div class="card-info mt-20 mb-20" data-v-10ba3bd0><p class="card-info-text" data-v-10ba3bd0><span data-v-10ba3bd0>Public health data integration and automation systems are crucial for effective healthcare delivery and public health surveillance. However, the factors associated with hospitals' adoption and successful implementation remain inadequately explored.</span></p> <div class="read-more" data-v-10ba3bd0><a href="/2026/1/e86263" aria-label="Continue reading this article" class="continue-reading" data-v-10ba3bd0><span aria-hidden="true" class="icon fas fa-long-arrow-alt-right" data-v-10ba3bd0></span></a></div></div></div> <div class="card-date-social mt-6 pb-10" data-v-10ba3bd0><time datetime="2026-02-06" class="mb-0" style="margin-top: 2px;" data-v-10ba3bd0>2026-02-06
                        </time> <span class="mx-1" style="margin-top: 2px;" data-v-10ba3bd0>|</span> <span class="sm-icons" data-v-10ba3bd0><a title="share-on-Bluesky" href="https://bsky.app/intent/compose?text=Check%20out%20this%20fascinating%20article%20by%20%40jmirpub.bsky.social!%20https%3A%2F%2Fojphi.jmir.org%2F2026%2F1%2Fe86263" aria-label="Share this item on Bluesky" data-test="bluesky-button" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank" class="bluesky small"><span class="screen-readers-only">Share on Bluesky</span></a> <a title="share-on-Twitter" href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=Check%20out%20this%20fascinating%20article%20by%20%40jmirpub!%20https%3A%2F%2Fojphi.jmir.org%2F2026%2F1%2Fe86263" aria-label="Share this item on Twitter" data-test="twitter-button" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank" class="twitter small"><span class="screen-readers-only">Share on Twitter</span></a> <a title="share-on-Facebook" href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?s=100&amp;u=https://ojphi.jmir.org/2026/1/e86263&amp;quote=Check%20out%20this%20fascinating%20article%20by%20%40jmirpub!" aria-label="Share this item on Facebook" data-test="facebook-button" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank" class="facebook small"><span class="screen-readers-only">Share on Facebook</span></a> <a title="Linkedin" href="https://www.linkedin.com/feed?shareActive=true&amp;text=Check%20out%20this%20fascinating%20article%20by%20%40jmirpub!%20https%3A%2F%2Fojphi.jmir.org%2F2026%2F1%2Fe86263" aria-label="Share this item on Linkedin" data-test="linkedin-button" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank" class="linkedin small"><span class="screen-readers-only">Share on LinkedIn</span></a></span> <span class="card-altmetric" data-v-10ba3bd0><div data-doi="10.2196/86263" data-test="altmetric-link" data-badge-type="2" data-hide-no-mentions="true" data-badge-popover="bottom" class="altmetric-embed" data-v-10ba3bd0></div></span></div> <a href="#open-peer-review" class="skip-link" data-v-10ba3bd0>Skip recent articles and go to articles open for peer-review section <span aria-hidden="true" class="icon fas fa-chevron-down" data-v-10ba3bd0></span></a></div><div aria-label="Card containing the image, related theme, title, short preview, date posted, shareable links and altmetric score" class="card mb-80" data-v-10ba3bd0><div class="card-header" data-v-10ba3bd0><div class="card-img" data-v-10ba3bd0><div data-v-10f10a3e data-v-10ba3bd0><img data-srcset="https://asset.jmir.pub/assets/d5c3e4a2e56efb16bc3d19326da2117e.png 480w,https://asset.jmir.pub/assets/d5c3e4a2e56efb16bc3d19326da2117e.png 960w,https://asset.jmir.pub/assets/d5c3e4a2e56efb16bc3d19326da2117e.png 1920w,https://asset.jmir.pub/assets/d5c3e4a2e56efb16bc3d19326da2117e.png 2500w" alt="Article Thumbnail" title="Fairness Correction in COVID-19 Predictive Models Using Demographic Optimization: Algorithm Development and Validation Study" aria-label="Article Thumbnail" src="https://asset.jmir.pub/placeholder.svg" data-v-10f10a3e></div> <div tabindex="0" role="button" aria-label="Open modal window to view the image" data-test="card-img-info" class="card-img-info" data-v-10ba3bd0><span aria-hidden="true" class="icon fas fa-search-plus" data-v-10ba3bd0></span></div></div></div> <div class="card-body mt-15" data-v-10ba3bd0><a href="/themes/1662" aria-label="Open theme with OJPHI Theme Issue: Opportunities and Challenges in the Application of AI in Public Health Informatics" class="link card-theme" data-v-10ba3bd0>
                            OJPHI Theme Issue: Opportunities and Challenges in the Application of AI in Public Health Informatics
                        </a> <div class="card-title" style="flex-grow: 1;" data-v-10ba3bd0><a href="/2026/1/e78235" data-test="card-title" aria-label="Fairness Correction in COVID-19 Predictive Models Using Demographic Optimization: Algorithm Development and Validation Study" title="Fairness Correction in COVID-19 Predictive Models Using Demographic Optimization: Algorithm Development and Validation Study" class="h5" data-v-10ba3bd0>
                                Fairness Correction in COVID-19 Predictive Models Using Demographic Optimization: Algorithm Development and Validation Study
                            </a></div> <div class="card-info mt-20 mb-20" data-v-10ba3bd0><p class="card-info-text" data-v-10ba3bd0><span data-v-10ba3bd0>COVID-19 forecasting models have been used to inform decision making around resource allocation and intervention decisions e.g., hospital beds or stay-at-home orders. State-of-the-art forecasting models often use multimodal data such as mobility or socio-demographic data to enhance COVID-19 case prediction models. Nevertheless, related work has revealed under-reporting bias in COVID-19 cases as well as sampling bias in mobility data for certain minority racial and ethnic groups, which affects the fairness of the COVID-19 predictions among racial and ethnic groups.</span></p> <div class="read-more" data-v-10ba3bd0><a href="/2026/1/e78235" aria-label="Continue reading this article" class="continue-reading" data-v-10ba3bd0><span aria-hidden="true" class="icon fas fa-long-arrow-alt-right" data-v-10ba3bd0></span></a></div></div></div> <div class="card-date-social mt-6 pb-10" data-v-10ba3bd0><time datetime="2026-02-03" class="mb-0" style="margin-top: 2px;" data-v-10ba3bd0>2026-02-03
                        </time> <span class="mx-1" style="margin-top: 2px;" data-v-10ba3bd0>|</span> <span class="sm-icons" data-v-10ba3bd0><a title="share-on-Bluesky" href="https://bsky.app/intent/compose?text=Check%20out%20this%20fascinating%20article%20by%20%40jmirpub.bsky.social!%20https%3A%2F%2Fojphi.jmir.org%2F2026%2F1%2Fe78235" aria-label="Share this item on Bluesky" data-test="bluesky-button" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank" class="bluesky small"><span class="screen-readers-only">Share on Bluesky</span></a> <a title="share-on-Twitter" href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=Check%20out%20this%20fascinating%20article%20by%20%40jmirpub!%20https%3A%2F%2Fojphi.jmir.org%2F2026%2F1%2Fe78235" aria-label="Share this item on Twitter" data-test="twitter-button" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank" class="twitter small"><span class="screen-readers-only">Share on Twitter</span></a> <a title="share-on-Facebook" href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?s=100&amp;u=https://ojphi.jmir.org/2026/1/e78235&amp;quote=Check%20out%20this%20fascinating%20article%20by%20%40jmirpub!" aria-label="Share this item on Facebook" data-test="facebook-button" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank" class="facebook small"><span class="screen-readers-only">Share on Facebook</span></a> <a title="Linkedin" href="https://www.linkedin.com/feed?shareActive=true&amp;text=Check%20out%20this%20fascinating%20article%20by%20%40jmirpub!%20https%3A%2F%2Fojphi.jmir.org%2F2026%2F1%2Fe78235" aria-label="Share this item on Linkedin" data-test="linkedin-button" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank" class="linkedin small"><span class="screen-readers-only">Share on LinkedIn</span></a></span> <span class="card-altmetric" data-v-10ba3bd0><div data-doi="10.2196/78235" data-test="altmetric-link" data-badge-type="2" data-hide-no-mentions="true" data-badge-popover="bottom" class="altmetric-embed" data-v-10ba3bd0></div></span></div> <a href="#open-peer-review" class="skip-link" data-v-10ba3bd0>Skip recent articles and go to articles open for peer-review section <span aria-hidden="true" class="icon fas fa-chevron-down" data-v-10ba3bd0></span></a></div><div aria-label="Card containing the image, related theme, title, short preview, date posted, shareable links and altmetric score" class="card mb-80" data-v-10ba3bd0><div class="card-header" data-v-10ba3bd0><div class="card-img" data-v-10ba3bd0><div data-v-10f10a3e data-v-10ba3bd0><img data-srcset="https://asset.jmir.pub/assets/85eb8dfa2b912fb09b2537b89fdd8b6c.png 480w,https://asset.jmir.pub/assets/85eb8dfa2b912fb09b2537b89fdd8b6c.png 960w,https://asset.jmir.pub/assets/85eb8dfa2b912fb09b2537b89fdd8b6c.png 1920w,https://asset.jmir.pub/assets/85eb8dfa2b912fb09b2537b89fdd8b6c.png 2500w" alt="Article Thumbnail" title="Demonstrating a Social Intelligence Analysis Framework for Loneliness: Infodemiology Approach" aria-label="Article Thumbnail" src="https://asset.jmir.pub/placeholder.svg" data-v-10f10a3e></div> <div tabindex="0" role="button" aria-label="Open modal window to view the image" data-test="card-img-info" class="card-img-info" data-v-10ba3bd0><span aria-hidden="true" class="icon fas fa-search-plus" data-v-10ba3bd0></span></div></div></div> <div class="card-body mt-15" data-v-10ba3bd0><a href="/themes/1415" aria-label="Open theme with Big Data for Health Promotion and Health Equity" class="link card-theme" data-v-10ba3bd0>
                            Big Data for Health Promotion and Health Equity
                        </a> <div class="card-title" style="flex-grow: 1;" data-v-10ba3bd0><a href="/2026/1/e59861" data-test="card-title" aria-label="Demonstrating a Social Intelligence Analysis Framework for Loneliness: Infodemiology Approach" title="Demonstrating a Social Intelligence Analysis Framework for Loneliness: Infodemiology Approach" class="h5" data-v-10ba3bd0>
                                Demonstrating a Social Intelligence Analysis Framework for Loneliness: Infodemiology Approach
                            </a></div> <div class="card-info mt-20 mb-20" data-v-10ba3bd0><p class="card-info-text" data-v-10ba3bd0><span data-v-10ba3bd0>Loneliness is a dynamic phenomenon that can be investigated using social media and web data.</span></p> <div class="read-more" data-v-10ba3bd0><a href="/2026/1/e59861" aria-label="Continue reading this article" class="continue-reading" data-v-10ba3bd0><span aria-hidden="true" class="icon fas fa-long-arrow-alt-right" data-v-10ba3bd0></span></a></div></div></div> <div class="card-date-social mt-6 pb-10" data-v-10ba3bd0><time datetime="2026-01-15" class="mb-0" style="margin-top: 2px;" data-v-10ba3bd0>2026-01-15
